<HEADLINE> China Beaten by Australia in Women Basketball </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, April 24 (Xinhua) -- China lost its opener 61-97 against
Australia in the four-nation International Women's Basketball
Competition in Osaka on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Michelle Griffiths scored the most of 16 points to pace
Australia for the victory.
</P>
<P>
In another match, the United States scored a 93-85 win over
host Japan as Lisa Leslie netted in 31 points.
</P>
<P>
Each squad will meet the other teams twice in the goodwill
series which runs to April 30. 
</P>
</TEXT>
