<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1500 GMT, April 24 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW -- The Russian State Duma Friday approved Sergei
Kiriyenko as prime minister in the third round of ballot to avoid
the disbanding of parliament's lower house, the balloting
commission announced.
</P>
<P>
Igor Bratischev, the commission chairman, said 315 deputies had
taken voting cards but only 276 deputies actually cast their
ballot. In this secret ballot, Kiriyenko had won 251 votes in the
Duma with 25 against.
</P>
<P>
He needs 226 votes in the 450-seat Duma irrespective of how
many take part in the ballot. (Russia-Duma-Approval)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TOKYO -- Visiting Chinese Vice-President Hu Jintao told a
press conference here Friday afternoon that he felt satisfied with
the result of his present Japan trip.
</P>
<P>
Hu said he had reached consensus on a series of major issues
with leaders of the Japanese government and political parties, as
well as people from various sectors.
</P>
<P>
Hu said the Chinese side holds that bilateral ties are
generally "satisfactory" while the two countries are constantly
expanding links in every field. (Japan-China-Hu)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MOGADISHU -- The 10 kidnapped aid workers
of the International Committee of the Red Cross (ICRC) were
officially released by their captors Friday.
</P>
<P>
The hostages were first moved from their place of captivity to
the ICRC run hospital of Keysaney, about a mile north of the
capital, where they were offered a little medical checkup and
refreshment drinks and food.
</P>
<P>
They were also given telephones to contact their offices and
relatives and a plane has been called for to lift them to
Nairobi. The aid workers who all looked healthy but tired were
extremely happy after nine days of captivity. (Somalia-aid workers
released)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
DAMASCUS -- Syrian President Hafez al-Assad held talks Friday
with visiting Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak on the Mideast
peace process, the Syrian News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The news agency did not disclose details of the talks in the
Mediterranean resort Latakia, to where Mubarak flew earlier in the
day.
</P>
<P>
Mubarak's visit is part of the two countries' efforts to
continue consultation and coordination over issues in the Middle
East, particularly the Israeli offer to carry out a conditional
withdrawal from south Lebanon. (Syria-Egypt-Talks) 
</P>
