<HEADLINE> Beijing Mayor Meets German Delegation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Beijing's Mayor Jia Qinglin met
here today with a delegation from Germany's Rhineland-Palatinate,
led by its Minister-President Kurt Beck.
</P>
<P>
Jia said that Beijing and Koln and Berlin are friendly cities
and he believes the visit will increase friendly ties.
</P>
<P>
Beck said that Germany's economy is developing very rapidly
like China's and he is willing to increase cooperation with
Beijing in the fields of trade, culture and industry.
</P>
<P>
Jia said that Beijing is now seeking new economic growth points
focusing on electronic information, modern agriculture, finance
and tourism and that he hopes foreign investors will have
extensive cooperation with Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Beck and his party are here at the invitation of the Chinese
People's Institute of Foreign Affairs. They will also visit
Shanghai and Fujian.  
</P>
