<HEADLINE> Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 24 (Xinhua) -- After 20 years of
reforms and opening up, China has basically established a lagal
system and laid a foundation for rule by law among the masses.
</P>
<P>
Chen Lijie, deputy director of the Law Department of the State
Economic and Trade Commission, made a remarks at a
symposium on rule by law held here recently.
</P>
<P>
She said that government departments are gradually shifting
their efforts from micro-economic controls and direct management
to macro-economic controls and indirect management and this means
that they will more rely on economic and legal means than on
administrative means.
</P>
<P>
Huang Huanliang, an official from the Ministry of Land and
Natural Resources, said at the symposium that legalizing
government intervention in the market economy means putting each
administrative office and administrative action of government
intervention in the market economy responsible to the law.
</P>
<P>
Laws and regulations on the market economy should be perfected
to ensure that administrative behavior has a legal basis, he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
