<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 6 Dead, 44 Missing In Northwest China Windstorm </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, April 24 (Xinhua) -- The windstorm that hit most of
northwest China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region last Sunday
left 6 dead, 44 missing and 256 injured, according to the latest
official figures.
</P>
<P>
The wind and sandstorm also caused heavy property losses in 52
cities and counties and affected 1.56 million people. Over 20,000
local residents suffered from illness after the disaster.
</P>
<P>
It damaged over 38,000 houses, over 10,000 tents and a large
number of communications and telecommunication facilities, and
power supplies. More than 99,000 head of livestock were killed by
the storm, which also caused 113 fires.
</P>
<P>
Official estimates put total losses at more than 1.1 billion
yuan.
</P>
<P>
Life in the stricken areas is returning to order thanks to
joint efforts by local governments, residents and army troops.
</P>
</TEXT>
