<HEADLINE> Four Injured in Train Derailment in Switzerland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, April 24 (Xinhua) -- At least four people were injured
Friday when a train rolling at 140 km/h between Switzerland's
western cities of Geneva and Lausanne derailed, according to Swiss
news reports.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the accident has yet to be known but a technical
problem seems to have played a part in the accident, the Swiss
French television quoted the railroad authorities as saying.
</P>
<P>
Another train derailed at the same site but caused no
casualties. Trains travelling between Geneva and Lausanne for
Friday Saturday has been disrupted or rescheduled. 
</P>
