<HEADLINE> Yi Jingqian Sails into Semis at ITF Women's Circuit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Home favorite Yi Jingqian took
the limelight here on Friday, romping top seed Asagoe Shinobu of
Japan to breeze into the semi-finals at the '98 ITF women's
circuit in China.
</P>
<P>
Yi Jingqian beat the strong winds patiently for a 6-4, 6-2
quarter-final victory, while Shinobu, No.10 on Japan's rankings,
was toppled by Yi's swift balls and her own errors caused
partially by the winds.
</P>
<P>
"Technically, we stayed at the same level, but she played worse
than I did against the winds," Yi, ranked 244th on the world, said
after the match.
</P>
<P>
Yi was the only Chinese woman sailing into the top four as her
teammates Ding Ding was eliminated by Morigami Akiko of Japan 1-6,
6-3, 0-6, and Li Li dispatched by third seed Kim Eun-Ha of South
Korea 1-6, 5-7.
</P>
<P>
Second seed American Shaughnessy Meghann won the first set 6-1
with ease before her rival Prakusya Wynne of Indonesia quitted due
to an injury.
</P>
<P>
Friday also featured one match of the doubles' semi-finals as
top seed Austrailan Barclay Catherine and South Korean Kim Eun-ha
eliminated their Japanese opponents 6-1, 6-4. 
</P>
</TEXT>
