<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Meeting To Mark China's Long March Rocket Launches </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 24 (Xinhua) -- China Aerospace Corp (CASC) held
a meeting here today to mark the 50 launches of Long March rockets
over the past 28 years.
</P>
<P>
Government officials and aerospace scientists attended the
meeting and talked about the development of China's aerospace
industry.
</P>
<P>
The first launch was on this day 28 years ago. A Dongfanghong-1
(East is Red) satellite was carried aboard a Long March-1 rocket
from the Jiuquan Satellite Launch Center in Gansu Province.
</P>
<P>
The event made China the fifth country in the world to launch a
domestic satellite on a domestic rocket, after the Soviet Union,
the United States, France and Japan.
</P>
<P>
By the 50th launch on March 26, Long March rockets had
successfully carried 50 satellites into orbit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
