<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Multimedia Industry Expected To Help China's Economy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Du Xunsheng, a State Economic and
Trade Commission official, speaking at a symposium on China's
strategy of developing the multimedia industry, said that China's
electronics market will be worth one trillion yuan by year 2000
and 6 trillion yuan by 2010 and that it will play a key role in
promoting China's economic growth.
</P>
<P>
He said that China will be the largest electronics information
market in the world in the next century and that China's
multimedia market has already entered a stage of rapid expansion.
</P>
<P>
Since the beginning of the 1990s, China's computer industry has
been expanding at an annual rate of more than 50 percent and China
now has over 20,000 enterprises and institutes in computer
development, production, sales, maintenance and consultation.
</P>
<P>
Since 1994, the Chinese government has listed multimedia
technology as a priority project in its technology development
plan and over the past several years, has focused on developing
multimedia chips, VCD machines, and multimedia computers.
</P>
<P>
Chinese information technology companies like Beijing Founder
Electronics Corporation Ltd, China Computer Software and
Technology Service Corporation, and the Legend Group are able to
compete with their international counterparts, and Chinese
computers account for 60 percent of China's market.
</P>
<P>
But China needs to develop its own information industry,
especially the multimedia industry, in order to survive and
prosper in the future world of information technology.
</P>
<P>
China will give priority to a nation-wide multimedia
information network, computer industry bases, the software
industry, smart-card businesses, and computer products and systems
for restructuring traditional industries.
</P>
<P>
Li Guojie, of the National Research Center for Intelligent
Computers, says that Chinese language processing is no longer the
advantage of Chinese IT companies and that Chinese companies have
to use multimedia as the core technology.
</P>
<P>
The symposium was part of the International Multimedia
Technology and Application Exhibition that is being held here from
Thursday to Monday.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
