<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Li Fang uprooted top
seed Sandrine Testud of France to book her semi-finals berth at
the Budapest Open women's tennis tournament here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Li Fang, sixth seed, rallied fron one set down to beat French
ace Testud, ranked 13th in the world, 5-7, 7-6 (7-5), 6-4 in a
three-hour marathon match.
</P>
