<HEADLINE> Positive Signs Emerged in CPC, CPJ Ties: Hu Jintao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, April 24 (Xinhua)-- Some positive signs have emerged in
the relations between the Communist Party of China (CPC) and the
Communist Party of Japan (CPJ).
</P>
<P>
Visiting Chinese Vice-President Hu Jintao said this at a press
conference here Friday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Hu, also member of Standing Committee of the Political Bureau
of the CPC Central Committee, said that the two parties had a
long-time contact in the past, but it was suspended later on.
</P>
<P>
Hu stressed that so long as the two parties proceed from the
overall situation of Sino-Japanese friendship and adhere to the
principles of independence, equality, mutual respect and
non-interference in each other's internal affairs, it is possible
to realize the normalization of bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
When asked to comment on the Sino-American and Sino-Japanese
relations, Hu said the U.S. is the largest developed country while
China is the largest developing country in the world. Anyone who
favors world peace, stability and development will support the
improvement of Sino-American relations, he noted.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, people who care about peace and stability in Asia
and the world will also support the further development of
Sino-Japanese relations due to the influential status of the two
countries in the world.
</P>
<P>
However, the development of Sino-American, Sino-Japanese and
even Japan-American ties should not be directed at a third party,
Hu said, adding that only with this point of view could all
parties join hands to build a new century of peace, stability,
prosperity and progress. 
</P>
</TEXT>
