<P>
Shen said the report, which was submitted to the Security Council
of the United Nations on April 19, 1998, covers a wide scope. It
contains not only an analysis of the sources of conflicts in
Africa and their consequences and an overview of the experiences
and lessons of the Council's response to these conflicts, but
also his views on Africa's economic and social development as
well as his hopes and expectations for African countries.
</P>
<P>
Shen said the Secretary-General has also put forward proposals
on peacekeeping, the promotion of socio-economic development, and
the role of the Council and other international bodies.  
