<BODY>
<HEADLINE> First Genocide Culprits Executed in Rwanda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, April 24 (Xinhua) -- The first 22 Rwandan genocide
culprits have been executed Friday at five different locations,
the Rwanda News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
In the capital Kigali, four were executed in front of a huge
crowd of over twenty thousand people.
</P>
<P>
The four executed outside the Nyamirambo Stadium included
Froduald Karamira, the deputy chairman of the "Hutu Power," a
faction of the MDR -- the Republican Democratic Party that
opposed the Arusha peace accord and called all Hutus to unite
against their common enemy, the Tutsis.
</P>
<P>
The executed also included Silas Munyagishari, former Kigali
prosecutor who during the genocide was the ring-leader of the
massacres of Tutsis in one of the suburbs of the capital,
Nyakabanda.
</P>
<P>
The third was a Burundian national, Elie Nhimiyimana, who
played a leading role in the genocide of Tutsis in Gikondo suburb
of the capital. The other was a woman, Virginie Mukankusi.
</P>
<P>
On Thursday night, a heavy security apparatus was deployed in
and around Nyamirambo suburb so as to prevent any terrorist act
that could hinder Friday's ceremonies.
</P>
<P>
Early Friday morning the whole capital Kigali was on the move,
triggering heavy traffic jams in all major arteries leading to
the site of execution.
</P>
<P>
At 10:15 am the culprits were brought in a heavily escorted
motorcade made of pick-ups, and a land-cruiser.
</P>
<P>
The culprits were first tied from ankles up to the neck, on
poles that were fixed early Friday morning.
</P>
<P>
They were then covered with a black veil before the firing
squad made of six policemen was deployed and started shooting one
culprit after another.
</P>
<P>
In Kigali, the huge crowd which attended the execution was
somewhat relieved to see the criminals punished. 
</P>
</TEXT>
