<HEADLINE> Yeltsin Satisfied with Result of Duma Premier's Vote </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin on
Friday expressed satisfaction at the result of the third vote by
the State Duma on his premier's nomination, according to the
Itar-Tass news agency.
</P>
<P>
The Duma approved Sergei Kiriyenko as prime minister by 251
voting for and 25 against in a closed ballot.
</P>
<P>
In a televised address Yeltsin described the confirmation of
Sergei Kiriyenko as prime minister as "a victory of reason over
emotions".
</P>
<P>
He said the approval was the understanding of the fact that the
political balance should be preserved and the government should be
granted a possibility to work normally.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin also expressed hope that the formation of most of the
government will be completed by the next weekend.
</P>
<P>
The president thought that the government's work is entering a
qualitarively new stage, and it is just a beginning.
</P>
<P>
Kiriyenko was officially appointed by the president as Russian
premier after the Duma's vote on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin also had a two-hour talks with the new prime minister
on the current situation and plans of the new government, the
presidential press service said. 
</P>
