<HEADLINE> Two Killed in Mosque Bomb Explosion in Yemen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANAA, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Two people were killed and 26
others were injured when a time bomb exploded inside a mosque in
Sanaa, the capital of Yemen on Friday, the Yemeni news agency
(YNA) reported.
</P>
<P>
The explosion took place in a corner of the Al Khair Mosque in
central Sanaa at 1:30 pm (local time) when the Muslim worshippers
were getting out, YNA quoted a senior official in the Interior
Ministry as saying.
</P>
<P>
The nationalities of the casualties were not yet available, but
it was reported that among the injured there were two
U.S. citizens, a Dutch, a Canadian and several Africans, the
officials said.
</P>
<P>
At least ten injured ones were in serious condition, security
officials said.
</P>
<P>
So far, no one claimed responsibility for the explosion.
</P>
<P>
Investigations were underway and the Yemeni government has vowed
to bring criminals before trial.
</P>
<P>
Yemen, a poor Gulf nation has been suffering from frequent
violence after the 1994 civil war, during which the conservative
northern Yemen destroyed the socialist south within the union and
reunified the country. 
</P>
