<HEADLINE> Ambassador Shen on China's Assistance to African Countries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Speaking at the United Nations Security Council's open debate
on Africa, Shen said in last year alone, China signed new
assistance agreements with 41 African countries.
</P>
<P>
Shen said to adapt to the changing situation, China reformed
the ways of providing aids and adopted additional methods,
namely, augmenting governmental assistance with the
involvement of financial institutions and companies.
</P>
<P>
The ambassador said China provided preferential government
loans to Africa and set up joint ventures or cooperative projects
with local enterprises for the execution of assistance projects.
</P>
<P>
Shen said the purpose was to help the recipient countries
develop productive projects based on local demand and resources,
enhance the efficiency of assistance, boost local employment and
at the same time, train African technical and managerial personnel.
</P>
<P>
Shen said China signed framework agreements with up to 20
countries in Africa with over 10 such projects already in
operation. China does not attach conditions to its assistance.
</P>
<P>
He said China will continue to enhance economic cooperation
and trade with African countries and support their efforts in
casting off poverty and realizing sustained economic development
at an early date.  
</P>
