Resolution 425, saying that it would pull back its troops from
south Lebanon after negotiating security arrangements with the
Lebanese government.
</P>
<P>
Lebanon and Syria firmly rejected the offer, urging Israel
to pull out its troops unconditionally in accordance with the
resolution 425.
</P>
<P>
Syria has great influence on Lebanon and is stationing more
than 30,000 troops there as peacekeepers.
</P>
<P>
Cairo expressed its support for the Syrian and Lebanese
position on the Israeli offer.
</P>
<P>
Israel has been occupying a 1,200-square-kilometer border strip
in south Lebanon since 1985 with the claimed aim to protect its
northern areas from Lebanon's guerrilla cross-border attacks.
