the U.N.'s call for the immediate withdrawal of special police
units and the call for Belgrade authorities to meet with Albanians
in an unconditional dialogue is the only solution to this
problem," Rubin said.
</P>
<P>
Senior administration officials said the U.S. will seek a
freeze on Yugoslav assets held overseas and a ban on international
trade with Belgrade, the administration officials said Friday.
</P>
<P>
Ambassador Robert Gelbard, chief U.S. mediator for the Balkans,
will propose the sanctions at a meeting Wednesday in Rome with
senior diplomats from Germany, Britain, Russia, Italy and France,
the so-called "Contact Group".
</P>
<P>
About 90 percent of the population of Kosovo is ethnic
Albanian. The Albanian extremists are seeking the region's
independence while the United States believes that Belgrade
should give them more autonomy. 
</P>
