<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Clan Fighting Continues in Somalia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Heavy fighting continues
Friday for the second day between militiamen from the sub-clans
of Majerten and Marehan in the village of Gobwein, 500 km South
of the capital Mogadishu.
</P>
<P>
According to sources from the region, the attack was launched
by the Majerten sub-clan dominating the town of Kismaio on the
Marehan sub-clan militia base in Gobwein.
</P>
<P>
In Thursday's fighting, the Marehan militiamen were forced to
retreat to the village of Yontoy, some 30 km North of Kismaio,
since the Majertens equipped with six battle wagons have been far
well organized for the operation than those of the Marehan
militiamen.
</P>
<P>
The fighting, which stopped as night has fallen, broken out
Friday with even more intensity. The Marehan militiamen who had
only four battle wagons have received some militia reinforcement
and pushed back the attack of the Majertens to Gobwein village.
</P>
<P>
Even though there are no exact casualty figures on either
side, a spokesman for the Marehan militiamen has claimed that
their forces have killed 17 men from the Majerten men.
</P>
<P>
The militia spokesman who spoke with the journalists had
admitted that his forces had lost 13 of their men during the
clashes since Thursday.
</P>
<P>
There's no official word from the Majertens themselves over
the fighting, however a VHF radio operator in Kismaio said
several wounded militiamen have been brought to the hospital of
the town, but no exact figure is available at this moment.
</P>
<P>
Both clansmen have nowadays been preparing for launching armed
insurgencies on the militia bases of the other.
</P>
<P>
General Mohamed Said Hirsi Morgan who controls the town of
Kismaio accused the Marehan fighters of threatening the security
in Lower Jubba Region by instigating armed clashes, while the
Marehans are on the contrary accusing General Morgan, the
son-in-law of Somalia's late dictator, of being behind all the
political difficulties between the two sides.
</P>
<P>
The fighting now between the two Darod sub-clans in Lower
Jubba is covering a very large area and displacing hundreds of
people. 
</P>
