The Dow slid as much as 123 points to 9,020 late in the session
before closing 78.71 points lower at 9,064.62. It finished the
week with a loss of 102.88. The blue-chip gauge set its record
9,184.94 Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Decliners outpaced advancers by more than a 2-to-1 margin on
the New York Stock Exchange, where volume totaled 632.27 million
shares as against 651.97 million in the previous session.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500-stock list fell 10.76 to 1,108.82,
and the NYSE composite index fell 6.08 to 574.47.
</P>
<P>
