<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, April 24 (Xinhua) -- The United States of
America welcomed the U.N. Secretary-General's report on Africa,
which established a solid foundation for discussing the future of
Africa, Bill Richardson, U.S. representative to the U.N., said
here Friday.
</P>
<P>
Richardson said the U.N. chief's report provides valuable
insights into the varied situation confronting Africa today. While
the report recognizes the historical failures of African countries
