<HEADLINE> Xiamen City Enjoys Robust Trade with Taiwan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, April 25 (Xinhua) -- Trade between the southeast China
port city of Xiamen and the island of Taiwan continues to
flourish.
</P>
<P>
According to local Customs statistics, the first quarter value
of exports to Taiwan hit 46 million US dollars, up 14.8 percent on
the previous year's period, with imports from Taiwan growing by
2.8 percent to 281 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The booming trade between Xiamen and Taiwan ignited in
April 1996, when the city government introduced various favorable
policies to expand trade with the island. Related policies
included lifting export restrictions, providing additional funding
for export enterprises and offering favorable tax rates.
</P>
<P>
The city's 1997 export volume to Taiwan reached 132 million
US dollars, up 85.7 percent on 1996.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
