<HEADLINE> Books, Photo Album In Memory of Veteran Revolutionary Peng Zhen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 25 (Xinhua) -- The Central Literature Publishing
House has recently released a book and a photo album to mark the
first anniversary of the death of China's veteran revolutionary
Peng Zhen.
</P>
<P>
With 55 articles, the book records great contributions Peng
made to Chinese liberation and modernization. The album has a
collection of 100 historical photos and over 20 original
handwriting works of the veteran who served as the chairman of the
Standing Committee of the National People's Congress in
1983-1988. 
</P>
