<HEADLINE> Jaermann Wins at Amstel Gold </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, April 25 (Xinhua) -- Switzerland's Rolf Jaermann won
the Amstel Gold Race in Maastricht, the Netherlands, to give the
Casino team its first ever World Cup victory.
</P>
<P>
Jaermann won by a wheel from his breakaway companion Maarten
den Bakker of Holland after 257 kilometers around Maastricht.
</P>
<P>
Italy's Michele Bartoli, who won the Liege-Bastogne-Liege race
last Sunday, finished in third about 20 seconds behind to retain
his lead in the World Cup standings.
</P>
<P>
The next race is not till August after major tours during the
Spring and early Summer so Bartoli is assured a long time on top
of the standings. 
