<HEADLINE> American Student Shoots Teacher to Death at Dance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 25 (Xinhua) -- A 14-year-old student opened
fire at a school dance in Pennsylvania Friday night, killing a
science teacher and wounding three others.
</P>
<P>
The 8th-grade student, identified by police as Andrew Jerome
Wurst, started the shooting at around 9:40 p.m. EDT Friday at
Nike's Place, a restaurant in Washington Township in Erie County,
the United Press International reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The 48-year-old teacher John Gillette of Edinboro at Parker
Middle School was shot to death on the stop. Two students and
another teacher were injured in the shooting.
</P>
<P>
The suspect fled the building after the shooting, but was
caught by the restaurant's owner, who was armed with a shotgun.
The teen surrendered his weapon and was handed over to police.
</P>
<P>
The motive for the shooting was not immediately known, but
Wurst told friends that he had planned to make the night
"memorable."
</P>
<P>
Wurst faces one charge of criminal homicide and eight related
counts of assault and illegal possession of a firearm. He is also
facing one drug charge, the report said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
