<HEADLINE> Belgian PM Nominates Replacing Cabinet Members </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, April 25 (Xinhua) -- Belgian Prime Minister Jean-Luc
Dehaene nominated two people Saturday to replace the resigning
ministers in the wake of the escape of the country's convicted
child rapist and killer.
</P>
<P>
The nominees are Louis Tobback for outgoing Deputy Prime
Minister and Interior Minister Johan Vande Lanotte and Tony van
Parys for outgoing Justice Minister Stefaan de Clerck.
</P>
<P>
The nomination was made and presented to King Albert II who
interrupted his vacation abroad and returned to his palace
following the news of the escape.
</P>
<P>
Vande Lanotte and de Clerck handed in their resignations after
Marc Dutroux managed to escape from a court at Neufchateau in
southeast Belgium and remained at large for three and a half hours
before being shot and recaptured by the Belgian police.
</P>
<P>
Dutroux was charged with killing four of the six young girls he
had abducted in mid-1996 when a nationwide child sex ring was
exposed and shocked the Belgian public.
</P>
<P>
The opposition parties called Friday for a vote of no
confidence on the current government and also demanded the prime
minister resign.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Dehaene promised that a no-confidence vote can
be held at the earliest next Tuesday. 
</P>
