<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Cancer Rehabilitation Center Opens in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 25 (Xinhua) -- A new cancer rehabilitation
center which entered operations today in Shanghai, China's largest
commercial center, will cater to the special needs of cancer
patients.
</P>
<P>
The center, funded by Shanghai Charity Fund and some 30-odd
enterprises and social organizations, will offer cancer sufferers
a place to communicate, exercise and receive rehabilitation
therapy.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the center's staff of a dozen medical experts will
provide both medical and psychological consulting.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai is on the list of Chinese cities with high cancer
rates, with a recent survey showing some 32,000 new cases of
cancer annually. The survey also revealed that some 23,000
Shanghainese die from cancer each and every year.
</P>
<P>
The cancer rehabilitation center has attracted extensive
attention from at home and abroad, according to informed sources.
</P>
<P>
A 24-member Japanese delegation of doctors and cancer patients
is scheduled to visit the center next week, with a Canadian
medical delegation set to visit in the near future. Numerous
cancer patients from throughout the country, including Taiwan,
have applied for treatment at the center. 
</P>
</TEXT>
