<HEADLINE> Birthday Celebrated for Oldest Giant Panda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, April 25 (Xinhua) -- The 36th birthday of Dudu, the
world's oldest giant panda, was celebrated on Friday with a tasty
cake served by zookeepers at the Zoo of Wuhan, capital of central
China's Hubei Province.
</P>
<P>
The female giant panda has lived at the zoo for 25 years and
remains in good health thank to the care and protection provided
by zookeepers.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that 117 giant pandas are currently housed in
zoos worldwide. Records indicate that only Dudu and three others
-- Lily (29) in Beijing, Qiangqiang (30) in Shenyang and Shasha
(32) in Taiyuan -- have lived above the age of 25. 
</P>
</TEXT>
