<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Charity Dinner Marks New HK Airport Completion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 25 (Xinhua) -- The completion of the new Hong
Kong International Airport at Chek Lap Kok was marked here
Saturday night by a charity dinner in the passenger terminal.
</P>
<P>
Jointly organized by the Airport Authority and the Community
Chest, the dinner was held in the building's spectacular Arrivals
Hall. Local television station TVB provided live entertainment for
the event, which was broadcast throughout Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
"The new airport is one of the greatest engineering projects
ever undertaken in Hong Kong," Tung Chee Hwa, chief executive of
the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR), told around
1,400 guests.
</P>
<P>
The 155-billion-HK-dollar (20 billion U.S. dollars) new airport
is one of the finest in the world, he said.
</P>
<P>
Airport Authority Chairman Wong Po-yan congratulated those who
have participated in the project: "After nine years of planning
and construction, the new Hong Kong International Airport is now
completed on schedule and within budget."
</P>
<P>
He thanked all those who have been involved in this project,
including experts and workers from all over the world, various
government departments, contractors and business partners.
</P>
<P>
The official new airport opening ceremony is being organized
separately by the SAR government and will be held close to the
actual opening date of July 6.
</P>
<P>
Over 4.5 million HK dollars (577,000 U.S. dollars) was raised
for the Community Chest through the sales of 142 banquet tables.
All proceeds will go toward the 140 social welfare agencies under
the umbrella of the charity organization. 
</P>
</TEXT>
