<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Syrian Vice President Visits Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 25 (Xinhua) -- Syrian First Vice President
Abdul-Halim Khaddam arrived here Saturday afternoon to exchange
views with Iranian officials on the developments of the Middle
East peace process.
</P>
<P>
Upon his arrival, Khaddam said that besides taking part in the
two countries' joint high committee, he would confer with Iranian
officials on "the issues of common interest."
</P>
<P>
It was believed that the Israeli proposal for conditional
withdrawal from south Lebanon would be top the agenda in
Khaddam's talks with Iranian officials. The latest development in
Iraq and the military cooperation between Turkey and Israel would
also be discussed.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli cabinet decided on April 1 to accept
U.N. Resolution 425, which called for unconditional withdrawal
from south Lebanon, but insisted on the negotiated security
arrangements by the Lebanese government.
</P>
<P>
Turkey and Israel have signed two military cooperation
agreements, arousing criticism from the Arab countries who fear
that Turkey is allying itself with the Jewish state against Arab
countries.
</P>
<P>
During his stay, Khaddam is scheduled to meet Iranian President
Mohammad Khatami. Syrian Foreign Minister Farouq al-Sharaa, who is
accompany Khaddam, will meet his Iranian counterpart Kamal
Kharrazi.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian-Syrian joint high committee meets every six months
in either of the two capitals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
