<HEADLINE> Guangzhou Launchs Image Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, April 25 (Xinhua) -- Guangzhou, capital of south
China's Guangdong Province, recently launched a major Image
Project as part of its bid to become a State-Level Civilized City
and prepare for the Ninth National Games scheduled for 2001.
</P>
<P>
Guangzhou will invest 42 billion yuan in the project designed
to transform itself into a beautiful and comfortable city,
according to local officials.
</P>
<P>
The program will include the construction of infrastructure,
stadiums and cultural facilities, as well as environmental
protection projects.
</P>
<P>
The city plans to increased the total coverage of urban
landscaped areas to 35 percent by the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
The city government plans to thoroughly clean all urban
districts, introduce orderly traffic flow and improve public
service facilities, including posts and telecommunications
departments and hospitals. 
