<HEADLINE> China Actively Explores New Export Markets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, April 25 (Xinhua) -- China is actively exploring new
export markets across the globe in order to minimize the
adverse effects of the financial crisis in Southeast Asia.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that the ongoing 83rd China Export
Commodities Fair, which opened 10 days ago, has attracted over
50,000 businesspeople from 164 countries and regions, with a
decrease in the number of buyers from Southeast Asian countries.
</P>
<P>
However, the number of customers from Africa, Latin America and
the Gulf region has increased, respectively by 39 percent, 17.75
percent and 31 percent, compared with the last fair.
</P>
<P>
A Saudi Arabian businessman, who attributed his attendance at
the fair to his admiration for Haier, China's first brand name
home electrical appliance, has already inked Haier
contracts valued at nine million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Rongshida, a major washing machine manufacturer in east China's
Anhui Province which attaches great importance to the development of
new products to fulfill the demand of new customers in Africa and
Latin America, has inked related contracts valued at over 10
million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
China's foreign trade departments dispatched trade delegations
to a number of countries, including Egypt and South Africa, prior
to this year's fair. The delegations focused on promoting Chinese
commodities and presented invitation letters to 5,000 foreign
importers.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that exports to Gulf nations, Africa, the
Commonwealth of Independent States and eastern Europe have grown
by 20 percent during this year's fair.  
</P>
</TEXT>
