<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-President Arrives in Osaka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OSAKA, Japan, April 25 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-President Hu
Jintao arrived here Saturday afternoon from Kyoto to continue his
six-day official good-will visit to Japan.
</P>
<P>
Osaka Governor Nokku Yokoyama hosted a banquet in honor of
Hu Saturday evening.
</P>
<P>
Also on Saturday, Hu paid his respects to a monument of the
late Chinese premier, Zhou Enlai, and visited two Japanese firms
in Kyoto before his departure for Osaka.
</P>
<P>
Osaka is the third leg of the Chinese Vice-president's Japan
tour. He is scheduled to leave here for Seoul on Sunday for an
official visit to the Republic of Korea. 
