the crown at the Belgrade Marathon on Saturday with a time of two
hours 12 minutes 51 seconds.
</P>
<P>
His compatriot Jimmy Muindi placed second with 2:13:03 and
Thabiso Moqhali of Lesotho was third in 2:13:11.
</P>
<P>
In the women's event, race favourite Irina Bogacheva of
Kyrgyzstan claimed the victory with a new course record at 2:32.07
</P>
<P>
Alena Peterkova of Czech Republic finsihed second in 2:34:09,
while Byelorussian Elena Makalova was third in 2:34:55. 
