<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-25 12:22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iran Against Transferring Oil Through Caspian Sea </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 25 (Xinhua) -- Iran's Deputy Foreign Minister
for Training and Research Affairs Gholamali Khoshroo reiterated
Saturday that Iran is against the proposed contract between
Turkmenistan and the U.S. on transferring oil through the Caspian
Sea.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian official news agency IRNA quoted Khoshroo as
saying that Iran opposes the contract because of its dangerous
ecological impacts.
</P>
<P>
Since the sea's movement is toward Iran, the country will be
more vulnerable to danger as a result of the transfer of oil through
pipelines on the Caspian Sea bed, he said, adding that the
slightest pollution will contaminate Iran's territorial waters.
</P>
<P>
Turkmenistan and the U.S. are reportedly trying to conclude a
contract on studying the possibility of laying pipelines on the
Caspian Sea bed to connect Turkmenistan and Azerbaijan for
transferring oil and gas.
</P>
<P>
Iranian Foreign Minister Kamal Kharrazi Wednesday announced
Iran's opposition to laying pipeline on the Caspian Sea bed,
saying that no party should take unilateral measures against the
rights of other littoral states of the sea.
</P>
<P>
Khoshroo also said that Iran is against unilateral utilization
of the Caspian Sea reserves and believed that any kind of
bilateral agreements in this respect must be approved by all the
five littoral states, namely, Iran, Azerbajan, Turkmenistan,
Russia and Kazakhstan.
</P>
<P>
He announced that the 6th seminar on Central Asia and Caucasia
will be held in Tehran on April 27-28 with the participation of
experts and researchers from 17 countries to review issues related
to energy and economy in the Caspian Sea as well as transfer of
oil and gas from this region.
</P>
<P>
He said the two-day seminar will discuss the role of regional
powers in resolving disputes and attaining economic development
and regional and extraterritorial viewpoints on security of the
Caspian Sea, oil and gas lines.
</P>
<P>
Due to the importance of the sea and under the proposal of the
participants, he said, a special gathering on economy and energy
in the Caspian Sea will be held on the sidelines of the
seminar. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
