<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Macao Exports Drop </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, April 25 (Xinhua) -- The export value of Macao between
January and February this year dropped by 10.4 percent from the
same period last year, the latest official statistics show.
</P>
<P>
According to figures released by the Macao Census and
Statistics Department on Friday nigh, exports in the first two
months of 1998 amounted to 2 billion patacas (about 250 million
U.S. dollars), down 236 million patacas (about 29.5 million
dollars) from a year earlier.
</P>
<P>
The value of imports also dropped in the period by 9.2 percent,
to less than 2 billion patacas.
</P>
<P>
As a result, Macao recorded a trade surplus of 73 million
patacas (about 9.1 million dollars), down 35 percent from the same
period last year.
</P>
<P>
The drop in exports and imports is believed to be a result of
the Asian financial crisis, analysts said.
</P>
<P>
About 81 percent of Macao's exports were garments and textile
goods, mainly to such destinations as the United States and the
European Union.
</P>
<P>
The leading import market for Macao was the Asian-Pacific
region, which supplied about 80 percent of its imported goods. The
imports of capital goods, raw materials and semi-finished and
consumer goods all declined. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
