<HEADLINE> Zambia to Auction Aid Fertilizers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, April 25 (Xinhua) -- The Zambian government will put
on public auction all fertilizers it receives as commodity aid
from donor nations instead of disbursing them as loans to traders
in the past.
</P>
<P>
According to the latest weekly Market Bulletin issued by the
Agricultural Market Information Center at the Ministry of
Agriculture, the fertilizers will be sold through auctioning.
</P>
<P>
The mechanism for auctioning aid commodities are being worked
out by the Ministry of Finance, said the bulletin.
</P>
<P>
"This is a departure from the system used to dispose last
year's commodity aid fertilizers which were disbursed as loans to
traders," it said.
</P>
<P>
The government has already received 23,000 tons of urea from
the Japanese grant and the aid commodity will be the first to be
auctioned, according to the bulletin. 
</P>
</TEXT>
