<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zanzibar to Host HIV/AIDS Workshop in May </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, April 25 (Xinhua) -- A workshop on HIV/AIDS
will be held next month in the isles of Zanzibar, the Guardian
reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The newspaper, citing a statement issued by the United Nations
Information Center, said that the workshop will be conducted by
the UN special sector based in Dakar of Senegal, which deals with
HIV/AIDS and social development.
</P>
<P>
The workshop will analyze the effects of HIV and propose plans
which the government, private sectors, non-governmental
organizations and donor agencies should follow to eradicate the
hazards of HIV and AIDS.
</P>
<P>
In major medical centers in Tanzania, such as Muhimbili,
Bugando and Bukoba, half of hospital beds are used by the HIV
infected patients leading to high costs of running health
services in the country, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
The statement further said that the hazards have hindered
economic development and caused discrimination and denial of
basic rights such as job opportunities, education and medical
treatment. A number of the infected persons have become social
outcasts.
</P>
<P>
The five-day workshop will be organized by the Zanzibar AIDS
Campaign Program, the newspaper said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980425.0139 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Purchase Scheme Helps HK Tenants Buy Homes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 25 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's director of housing
said here Saturday that many former tenants of the Housing
Authority have realized the dream of owning their own homes
thanks to the smooth implementation of the Tenants Purchase Scheme
(TPS).
</P>
<P>
More than 190 former tenants at the six estates scheduled for
the first phase of the TPS, which was launched by the government
last January, have recently executed their assignments to join the
ranks of Hong Kong's proud home owners, Tony Miller told a
ceremony to mark the birth of the first batch of TPS home owners.
</P>
<P>
Under the TPS, more than 26,000 families from six estates were
invited to buy their own rental units at very attractive prices,
set at 12 percent of the assessed market value.
</P>
<P>
Miller reaffirmed the contribution of the TPS in fulfilling the
government's target of achieving 70 percent home ownership by
2007.
</P>
<P>
"The TPS has enjoyed overwhelming support from prospective
purchasers. So far, over 12,000 families have already made formal
applications for purchase while tenants from estates not yet
selected have also indicated strong interest in early inclusion in
the scheme," he said.
</P>
<P>
"Another 84,000 families are expected to benefit from the TPS
in the next three years in line with the long-term objective of
providing at least 250,000 families the opportunities for home
ownership over a 10-year period," he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
