<HEADLINE> Marchers Against Child Labor Arrive in Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 25 (Xinhua) -- Thirty-four Asian participants in
a global march against child labor have arrived in Iran from
Pakistan through Mirjaveh border point in the southeastern
province of Sistan-Baluchesan.
</P>
<P>
Iran's official news agency IRNA Saturday quoted the
coordinator of the march in Iran, Saeed Neshat, as saying that 10
children from Iran's capital of Tehran came to the southeastern
province to welcome and join the marchers who arrived on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Asian marchers started their journey from the Philippine
capital of Manila in January and have so far passed through
Thailand, Singapore, Cambodia, Vietnam, Malaysia, Nepal,
Bangladesh, India and Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
The Latin American leg of the global march started on February
25 in Brazil and the African march began on March 21. In Europe,
the march is due to start on May 1.
</P>
<P>
All four groups of the marchers will converge in Geneva in the
first week of June when the International Labor Organization
is to draft a new convention against child labor.
</P>
<P>
Media Reports said that some 250 million underage children are
working worldwide. 
</P>
</TEXT>
