<HEADLINE> Intra-Afghan Dialogue to Start Sunday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, April 25 (Xinhua) -- Afghanistan's Taliban militia
and rival Northern Alliance will begin here Sunday their first
face-to-face talks in more than a year, a Pakistani Foreign Office
spokesman said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
"The first session of the (Afghan Joint) Steering Committee
will start here Sunday at 10 a.m.," the spokesman announced when
addressing a news conference Saturday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
He said the two sides of the Afghan political divide are
getting together here in a preparatory process in the form of the
steering committee for eventual substantive negotiations to
promote the peace process.
</P>
<P>
He said Pakistan is playing host to the first formal meeting
between the Taliban and representatives of Northern Alliance
leaders.
</P>
<P>
"The steering committee is primarily to discuss and finalize
the modalities for the meeting of the Afghan Ulema (religious
scholar)," the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
The meeting between the Taliban and the Northern Alliance was
made possible after hectic diplomatic efforts by the United
Nations, the Organization of the Islamic Conference, Pakistan,
Iran and other countries which have influence on Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
It was first announced that the Afghan Joint Steering Committee
would meet here Saturday. However, according to sources in the
Foreign Office, the Taliban delegation will not reach here until
3:30 p.m. Saturday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The Ulema Commission, which was proposed by the Taliban, will
bear the responsibility of deciding the future political setup in
Afghanistan if and when it is established.
</P>
<P>
However, there have been some differences between the Taliban
and the Northern Alliance on the agenda of the talks.
</P>
<P>
The Taliban Friday reiterated their stance that the main item
on the talks agenda should be the formation of the Ulema
Commission while the Northern Alliance has emphasized that the
meeting should also deliberate on a cease-fire and exchange of
prisoners. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
