<HEADLINE> Explosion Kills 5 in Nigeria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Five persons were killed and 14
others seriously injured when a suspected bomb exploded Thursday
night in the ancient city of Ile-Ife, in southwest Nigeria's Osun
State.
</P>
<P>
Media reports said the incident occurred around 8:00 p.m. at a
busy spot in the Sabo area of the town, causing demages to nearby
vehicles and buildings.
</P>
<P>
