Kuwait's representative Sheikh Ahmad Al-Fahad
Al-Sabah. U.S. President Bill Clinton agreed in March to allow
Thailand to cancel the deal because of Thailand's economic crisis
and decided not to impose a 250-million-dollar fine for the
cancellation. But the U.S. made it clear that Thailand would not
get its deposit back unless it resells the jets to a third
party. (Thailand-Kuwait-Jets)
</P>
