<DOCNO> XIE19980425.0174 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Police Develops Technique for Distinguishing Prints </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, April 25 (Xinhua) -- Chinese police have
developed four techniques to distinguish finger or foot prints
left by criminals.
</P>
<P>
With several pieces of test papers, an amount of special
powder, liquid and a hair-drier, policemen can make the finger or
foot prints of criminals clearly appear within 30 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Luo Ruibiao, an engineer with the public security bureau of
Xinji City of north China's Hebei Province, and his colleagues
have developed techniques for distinguishing dust, blood prints as
well as sweat and body fluid traces.
</P>
<P>
He said finger and foot prints are important evidence for
determining criminals. However, it has long been an headache for
police that it is not easy to distinguish fingerprints on dust,
foot prints on glazed tiles and blood fingerprints on dark and
rough materials.
</P>
<P>
The four techniques have recently passed appraisal by the
Ministry of Public Security. The ministry has decided to spread
the techniques in public security organs nationwide. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980425.0175 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Develops System to Monitor Deforms of Dams </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, April 25 (Xinhua) -- Chinese scientists have
developed a system that could automatically display the deforms of
a power station dam or a bridge accurately.
</P>
<P>
With the installation of the system, technicians can observe
even a millimeter-size deform of a dam or a bridge one kilometer
away.
</P>
<P>
The system is developed by Zhang Xuezhuang, a professor at
Central-South China Engineering University in Shangsha City of
central China's Hunan Province after more than 25 years research,
in cooperation with a hydroelectric engineering company and an
electronics research institute.
</P>
<P>
The system has just passed appraisal by experts who suggest
early application of the system in deformation monitor of dams of
power stations and slopes.
</P>
<P>
Experts believed that the system could find problems earlier
and technicians could adopt prevention measures timely, in order
to guarantee the safety of the power stations and bridges. 
</P>
</TEXT>
