<HEADLINE> Qinghai Discovers More Oil and Gas Reserves </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'NING, April 25 (Xinhua) -- Northwest China's Qinghai
Province set a record in oil and gas discovery, and its combined
oil and gas reserve increased by 70 million tons last year.
</P>
<P>
The figure accounted for 10 percent of the country's total for
the year, according to sources with the Qinghai Provincial
Petroleum Administration.
</P>
<P>
The Qinghai Oilfield, located in the Qiadam Basin in the
northern part of the Qinghai-Tibet Plateau, reported an increase
of 40-odd million tons of oil and gas reserves last year, the
sources said.
</P>
<P>
This made Qinghai Province the fourth largest oil and gas
center in China after Sichuan Province, the Shaanxi-Gansu-Ningxia
Region, and Tarim Basin in the Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, two gas pipelines of 300 km and a gas-power plant
have been built. The province will start building a third pipeline
and a plant with an annual production capacity of 100,000-ton
menthanol within this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
