<HEADLINE> French Frigate to Visit Kuwait </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, April 25 (Xinhua) -- French frigate "Floreal" will
arrive at the Kuwaiti Shuwaikh port Sunday to participate in a
joint military exercise between Kuwaiti and French navies, French
embassy sources said here Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The frigate, commissioned in May 1992 with its home port being
in French La Reunion Island, was designed to be permanently
deployed overseas and has been dedicated to a specific task,
namely to control maritime areas overseas where France has
interests, according to the sources.
</P>
<P>
The frigate is a surveillance warship with the capability to
search for and gather information. It can also carry out such
missions as navigation control, fishery protection and necessary
use of force to fight for French interests in the vicinity of
French overseas territories or in any maritime theater far from
Europe.
</P>
<P>
Kuwait and France signed a defense cooperation agreement
following the Gulf War in 1991 when the allied forces led by the
U.S. liberated the Gulf state from a seven-month Iraqi
occupation. 
</P>
