<DOCNO> XIE19980425.0199 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Implement New System in Loan Classification </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 25 (Xinhua) -- A new system for commercial banks
to classify their loans has been initiated in China in a bid to
strengthen credit management, improve loan classification and
enhance credit asset quality.
</P>
<P>
The People's Bank of China (PBOC) today issued a norm on the
new classification system, according to which bank loans will be
classified into standard, special mention, substandard, doubtful
and loss.
</P>
<P>
The PBOC said that the new system is designed to reach three
targets: to reveal the actual value and risk degree of loans and
reflect the quality of loans in a real, comprehensive and dynamic
way; to discover problems in loan granting, management,
supervision, recovery and the management of unperforming loans;
and to provide the basis for judging the sufficiency of reserves
for bad loans.
</P>
<P>
The PBOC demanded that to ensure the reliability of the new
classification system, all commercial banks should standardize
their management and operational practices.
</P>
<P>
Commercial banks are also required to classify all of their
loans for at least every six months, and the central bank will
supervise loan quality of commercial banks through spot inspection
and non-spot monitoring.
</P>
<P>
The PBOC'S spot inspection of bank loans will be carried out at
least once a year, and stricter control will be laid on commercial
banks which are found to have serious problems with loan
quality. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
