<DOCNO> XIE19980425.0200 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sun Yatsen's State Strategy Map Discovered </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, April 25 (Xinhua) -- A state strategy map designed
by Sun Yatsen, fore-runner of China's democratic revolution, was
discovered in Puyang County Archives in central China's Henan
Province.
</P>
<P>
The map included one main chart and 15 other subsidiary
charts. The map, 114 centimeters long and 105 meters wide,
describes the country building plan in 10 fields covering
communications, commercial ports, railways, water resources, iron
and steel, agriculture, forestry and irrigation.
</P>
<P>
The scale of the map is 1:390,000 and it was compiled by Tu
Sicong a cartographer and published by a Shanghai publishing house
in August 1929.
</P>
<P>
The map has a 7,000-ward introduction. The map especially has a
very detailed introduction of communications and commercial port
building.
</P>
<P>
Experts here said the map in fact reflected the strategy of
saving the nation with the boosting of industry and commerce,
which vividly described Sun Yatsen's grand ideal.
</P>
<P>
Sun was the leader of the 1911 Revolution, which is regarded as
the beginning of the country's democratic revolution. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
