<HEADLINE> First China-made 29-inch TV Picture Tube Produced </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, April 25 (Xinhua) -- The first China-made
large-screen color TV picture tube was recently produced by a
state-owned enterprise in Anyang, central China's Henan Province.
</P>
<P>
It marks the ending of the country's absolute dependence on
importing picture tubes of the kind in color TV production, said a
government official in charge of electronic industry.
</P>
<P>
The 29-inch picture tube was manufactured in a newly-built
screen furnace, believed to be the largest of its kind in Asia, at
the Anbo Company, China's largest color picture tube maker, which
had accumulated assets of 4.2 billion yuan since it was founded in
1991.
</P>
<P>
To conduct mass production, the company has set up three
production lines, two processing lines and a new workshop with a
total floor space of 33,000 sq.m.
</P>
<P>
The company is expected to produce 2.5 million 29-inch picture
tubes annually to meet the demand of seven domestic production
lines. 
</P>
