<HEADLINE> Myanmar Seizes 600 Kilograms of Drugs in March </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, April 25 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar authorities seized 600
kilograms of narcotic drugs, including 56 kilograms of heroin and
444 kilograms of opium, in the country in March, the official New
Light of Myanmar newspaper reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The seizures, made by army units, police and the customs
department, also included 245 liters of phensedyl, 140,291 tablets
of amphetamine stimulant drug and other chemicals.
</P>
<P>
During the month, combined teams destroyed a total of 56.55
hectares of poppy plantations in the eastern Shan State and Kachin
State, and army units destroyed four heroin refinery camps, the
report said.
</P>
<P>
The authorities took action against 355 people in connection
with 263 drug-related cases.
</P>
<P>
According to an earlier official report, the authorities seized
and destroyed more than 3,700 kilograms of heroin, more than
22,700 kilograms of opium and over 10 million tablets of stimulant
drugs during the period between September 1988 and the end of
December 1997. 
</P>
