<HEADLINE> Myanmar Leader Than Shwe Leaves for Visit to Brunei </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, April 25 (Xinhua) -- Chairman of the Myanmar State
Peace and Development Council (SPDC) Senior-General Than Shwe left
here Saturday for a state visit to Brunei.
</P>
<P>
Accompanying Than Shwe are SPDC First Secretary
Lieutenant-General Khin Nyunt, Foreign Minister U Ohn Gyaw and
other government ministers.
</P>
<P>
It is Than Shwe's second trip to a fellow member state of the
Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) this year after the
Philippines.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar and Brunei have few bilateral links. The two countries
initiated an air service agreement to establish the air link
between them in September 1996.
</P>
<P>
A visit by Brunei deputy foreign minister Haji Awang Mohd Daud
to Myanmar in November last year has strengthened the two
countries' bilateral ties. 
</P>
</TEXT>
