<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Uruguay Announces Economic Reform Plan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO, April 24 (Xinhua) -- The Uruguayan government
announced a plan Friday to accelerate economic reforms and improve
the competitivity of public and private enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The plan aims at maintaining the momentum of economic
transformations and reducing unemployment and inflation. It will
also tighten the control of the budget through the reduction of
public and private indebtedness and improve the situation of those
with the lowest income.
</P>
<P>
The government decided, in relation to the economic reforms, to
curb the public monopoly and promote private investment in the
fields of insurance, port services, alcohol and communications.
</P>
<P>
At the same time the government will continue concessions of
public services and works to private interests, such as road
maintenance, road and bridges building, ports and airports
operation, railroad transport, forest administration, water and
sewage works and gas pipelines.
</P>
<P>
The government will also take new measures to provide more
transparency and security to the credit market and long term
investment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
