<HEADLINE> Kenya: Coordinated Approach Towards Humanitarian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, April 24 (Xinhua) -- A coordinated approach
towards humanitarian assistance in Africa should be continuously
sought, Kenyan delegate Njuguna Mahugu said here Friday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the U.N. Security Council's open debate on the U.N.
chief's report on Africa, Mahugu said human rights missions should
be be deployed in Africa, thereby providing substantive
international pressure on the combatants to respect the human
rights of civilians.
</P>
<P>
The delegate said his country endorsed the U.N. chief's notion
of children as "zones of peace" and supported the idea of
establishing an international mechanism to assist host governments
on maintaining the security and neutrality of refugee camps.
</P>
<P>
Furthermore, he said, a focused attempt must be found to deal
with the impact of so-called "armed labor" or displaced persons
roaming across borders with weapons, which had the potential to
destabilize entire subregion. 
</P>
</TEXT>
