<HEADLINE> France Wins European Gymnastics Team Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 24 (Xinhua) -- France beat favourites Russia to
win the men's team title at the European Gymnastics Championships
in St Petersburg on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The French, led by former Russian champion Dmitry Karbanenko,
overwhelmed the defending champions by just 0.014 points, scoring
164.823 after six rotations.
</P>
<P>
Germany, with 164.033 points, took the bronze, while Bulgaria
were a distant fourth with 163.160.
</P>
<P>
France were in the lead by just 0.003 points before the final
rotation -- the high bar routine -- while the Russians were
competing on the pommel horse.
</P>
<P>
It all came down to both teams' leading gymnasts -- Karbanenko
and world and Olympic champion Alexei Nemov of Russia.
</P>
<P>
When Nemov fell off the pommel horse and Karbanenko made a
clean dismount of the high bar, it was clear who had clinched the
title.
</P>
<P>
The French, who defeated the Russian team on Thursday in the
team's junior competition, won their second team gold medal in two
days. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
