<HEADLINE> China's Medium, Small Enterprises to Get More Financial Support </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 25 (Xinhua) -- China's financial arms will soon
adopt a series of new policies to further support the healthy
development of medium and small enterprises, according to a senior
official with the People's Bank of China (PBOC).
</P>
<P>
Vice-Governor of PBOC Shang Fulin said that medium and small
enterprises play a significant role in the economy. Under China's
present situation, promoting the development of medium and small
enterprises will be a big help to reach this year's economic
growth target, and will create more jobs and help reduce financial
risks.
</P>
<P>
Shang said that China's financial institutions have always
supported the development of medium and small enterprises,
providing them with huge amounts of loans and a wide range of
financial services.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that by the end of March this year, the amount
of outstanding loans from state-owned commercial banks to medium
and small enterprises was about 1.7 trillion yuan, constituting
some 38 percent of the total amount of outstanding loans of
state-owned commercial banks.
</P>
<P>
In addition, commercial banks have been active in providing
medium and small enterprises with account transference,
remittance, settlement, information, management consultation and
other necessary services, he said.
</P>
<P>
He said that the PBOC is to adopt a series of policies in favor
of the development of medium and small enterprises, which involve
the rational increase of loans, the improvement of financial
services and the further improvement of the financial service
system.
</P>
<P>
He also stressed that while giving support to medium and small
enterprises, attention should be paid to preventing financial
risks with loans granted to these enterprises. 
</P>
</TEXT>
