<DOCNO> XIE19980425.0244 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fiat Posts Growth in First Quarter Sales, Pre-tax Profit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Fiat, Italy's leading private
industrial group, Friday reported good performance in the first
quarter this year with a growth in sales and pre-tax earnings.
</P>
<P>
Sales soared by 10.7 percent to 23.072 trillion lire (13
billion U.S. dollars) and pre-tax profits by 32 percent to 655
billion lire (369 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
In the corresponding period last year, sales were 20.844
trillion lire (11.7 billion U.S. dollars) and pre-tax profit 495
billion lire (278.9 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The group boasted that it stood in "a sharply more positive
financial position compared to the same period of the previous
year".
</P>
<P>
Sales of Fiat automobiles, its core business, grew by 7.1
percent, Iveco trucks and industrial vehicles by 13 percent and
tractors and other agricultural machinery by 12 percent.
</P>
<P>
The board of directors approved a dividend of 120 lire per
share of common and preferred stocks and 150 lire for each savings
share, against 100 and 130 respectively in the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Dividend payments will move from 522.8 billion lire (294.5
million U.S. dollars) to 684.7 billion (385.7 million
U.S. dollars), a growth of 33 percent, thanks in part to the
completion of a share capital increase in which one new share was
issued free for every ten already held by shareholders. 
</P>
</TEXT>
