<DOCNO> XIE19980425.0246 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Higgins Through to Last Eight at World Snooker </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 24 (Xinhua) -- World number three John Higgins of
Britain won through to the quarter-finals of the World Snooker
Championship in Sheffield, England on Friday thanks to three
century breaks against his compatriot Anthony Hamilton.
</P>
<P>
Higgins defeated Hamilton 13-9 to reach the last eight of the
tournament for the third successive year.
</P>
<P>
Defending champion Ken Doherty is just three frames away
from joining Higgins in the quarter-finals.
</P>
<P>
The Irishman powered his way to a 10-3 lead over Stephen Lee,
with seven half-century breaks and a superb 137 in the ninth
frame.
</P>
<P>
Lee closed the gap by taking the final three frames of the
night, but with the score 10-6 overnight, Doherty remains the
favourite to go through.
</P>
<P>
He requires three of Saturday afternoon's nine frames to
win. Earlier, Mark Williams built up a commanding 11-5 lead over
six-times world champion Steve Davis while John Parrott is 5-3
ahead of Malta's Tony Drago. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
