<HEADLINE> Yugoslav Army Kill 16 Ethnic Albanian Infiltrators </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Frontier troops of the Yugoslav
army killed at least 16 ethnic Albanian infiltrators in foiling
infiltration attempts by some 200 ethnic Albanian gunmen in a
border area on Thursday and Friday.
</P>
<P>
A communique released by the headquarters of the general staff
of the Yugoslav army said the Yugoslav army repulsed the attack of
the ethnic Albanian gunmen near Kosara village bordering Albania,
and that no Yugoslav soldiers were killed or injured.
</P>
<P>
The frontier troops captured two of the infiltrators and seized
a great deal of weapons and ammunition in the fighting, the
communique said.
</P>
<P>
It said the captured infiltrators confessed they were Kosovo
Albanians who illegally entered Albania, where they received
military training.
</P>
<P>
The Yugoslav Foreign Ministry Friday lodged a protest with the
Albanian ambassador to Yugoslavia on the illegal entry of the
armed Kosovo Albanians from Albania. Albania has denied the
charge.
</P>
<P>
In Washington, U.S. State Department spokesman James Rubin said
there had been "myriad deaths" in the border clash and that the
United States would press for new sanctions on Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
The Kosovo province of Serbia is populated mainly by ethnic
Albanians demanding independence. In recent months, armed ethnic
Albanian guerrillas have begun fighting against the federal
government. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
