<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Telephone Manufacturers Fighting for Market Share </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 25 (Xinhua) -- People say if 1997 was the year
for different brands of video compact disc (VCD) players, then the
year of the tiger, 1998, will be known as the year for telephone
manufacturers.
</P>
<P>
Up to now, all of China's major telephone manufacturers have
tried to obtain a bigger chunk of the market.
</P>
<P>
The Idall Electrical Appliance Company, a VCD giant, announced
it will elevate its share of telephones in the total product
spectrum to what is equivalent to VCD players.
</P>
<P>
The announcement was made not long after it became the "king of
bidding" for advertising vacancies in prime time slots on China
Central Television, a nationwide TV network.
</P>
<P>
A senior manager with BBK (Higher Step by Step in Chinese)
Electronic Industry Corp. said the telephone is an opportunity for
his company to follow the electronic game machine and the VCD
player. It is determined to make ever higher gains in the
telephone market.
</P>
<P>
BBK telephones had the best performance in terms of sales
volume last year. Industry analysts attribute this to its TV
commercial that swept the country with the "Did the stock market
climb again?" line.
</P>
<P>
The great market potential for telephones in China has drawn
many enterprises into this business, according to an official in
the market department of China General Corp. of Posts and
Telecommunications Industry.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show less than 10 percent of Chinese households have
installed telephones, and 15 million telephones find their homes
every year.
</P>
<P>
To date, more than 300 enterprises are involved in telephone
manufacturing, and others are entering the market.
</P>
<P>
Industry analysts say businesses, young or old, big or small,
are able to find a position in the competitive market because this
sector is not technology or investment intensive.
</P>
<P>
TCL Corp., which claims to control 17.01 percent of the
telephone market, is aware of the challenges from its many
competitors.
</P>
<P>
Apart from continuing to pursue flexible marketing methods, TCL
invested 10 million yuan in various kinds of advertising from last
year to early this year.
</P>
<P>
China is now the world's largest telephone producer. It
manufactures and sells 100 million telephones annually, accounting
for nearly half of the global figure.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
