<DOCNO> XIE19980425.0251 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Environmental Foundation Celebrates Fifth Anniversary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 25 (Xinhua) -- A top Chinese legislator sent a
congratulatory message today to the China Environmental Protection
Foundation (CEPF) praising the non-governmental organization on
its fifth anniversary.
</P>
<P>
In his letter, Tian Jiyun, a member of the Political Bureau of
the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC) and
vice-chairman of the Standing Committee of the National People's
Congress (NPC), praised the CEPF for its efforts in environmental
protection during the past five years.
</P>
<P>
"With economic development, much greater efforts will be needed
in environmental protection," Tian said.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope that the foundation will contribute more
to a cleaner environment.
</P>
<P>
The CEPF, established in April of 1993, is China's first
national environmental foundation. It has raised more than 12
million yuan and spent more than 3 million yuan in the promotion
of China's environmental protection drive.
</P>
<P>
Qu Geping, chairman of the NPC's Environmental and Resources
Protection Committee, and Xie Zhenhua, director of the State
Environmental Protection Administration, planted trees to
celebrate the foundation's fifth anniversary.  
</P>
</TEXT>
