<HEADLINE> Beijing Witnesses Record Increase in Exports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 25 (Xinhua) -- Beijing witnessed a record
increase in exports in the first three months of this year,
according to the Beijing Municipal Committee of Foreign Trade and
Economic Cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Beijing scored an export volume of 640 million US dollars in
the first quarter, 25.7 percent more than that for the same period
of last year.
</P>
<P>
The total import and export volume reached 1.334 billion US
dollars, up 15.8 percent, said Zhang Xuequn, an official from the
committee.
</P>
<P>
Zhang said that exports of state-owned enterprises reached 359
million US dollars, edging up by 30.8 percent compared with the
corresponding period of last year.
</P>
<P>
Increases of 21.8 percent and 69.2 percent were also scored in
exports of processing industry and electromechanical products in
the first three months of the year.
</P>
<P>
According to Zhang, exports of foreign-funded enterprises rose
by 20.7 percent, reaching 274 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Foreign investment for the first quarter reached 94 million US
dollars, up 15 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
