<HEADLINE> Beijing University Builds Largest College Library in Asia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 25 (Xinhua) -- A new library at Beijing
University, with a total floor space of 27,000 square meters and
keeping 3 million books, has been built just prior to the
centennial anniversary of the establishment of the university,
which falls on May 4.
</P>
<P>
Thus, the combined floor space of Beijing University's new and
old libraries has exceeded 50,000 square meters, with over 4,500
seats and the total number of books surpassing 7 million, the
largest in Asia.
</P>
<P>
The new library features a style of traditional Chinese
architecture. The latest electronic equipment and automatic
systems have been installed to offer modern services to readers.
</P>
<P>
Construction of the new library started in June 1996, and its
total investment was 100 million yuan (12 million US dollars),
including 10 million US dollars donated by Li Ka-shing, a Hong
Kong entrepreneur.  
</P>
</TEXT>
