<HEADLINE> Thunder Storm and Hail Hit Central China City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 25 (Xinhua) -- Nine people were killed in a hail
storm that struck Changde city in central China's Hunan Province
Thursday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
According to the local meteorological bureau, the thunder storm
brought with it a whole gale in some areas of the city, and
hailstones with a diameter of up to eight centimeters.
</P>
<P>
Some counties were hit by a tornado.
</P>
<P>
The storm demolished houses and flattened farm fields.
Transport and telecommunications were disrupted.
</P>
<P>
A report from the bureau says some business operations had to
be shut down, and students in 420 schools had to stay at home.
</P>
<P>
Local government officials rushed the disaster areas to guide
relief operations. Production was resumed soon after.  
</P>
</TEXT>
