<HEADLINE> Austria Backs Ukrainian EU, WTO Membership Quest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Austrian Prime Minister Viktor Klima
said here on Friday that his country will actively help step up
Ukrainian efforts to join the European Union.
</P>
<P>
Klima made these remarks at a joint press conference with his
Ukrainian counterpart Valery Pustovoitenko, adding that Austria
also supports Ukrainian entry into the World Trade Organization.
</P>
<P>
As the presidency state of the EU in the second half of 1998,
Austria would help Ukraine eliminate trade barriers and improve
the investment environment to promote the implementation of
partnership pacts between the EU and Ukraine, said Klima.
</P>
<P>
Pustovoitenko said that at the second summit meeting of all EU
members and Ukraine later this year in Austria, the possibility of
Ukrainian EU membership will be further considered.
</P>
<P>
Klima's two-day visit to Ukraine also included the meeting
Ukrainian President Leonid Kuchma and Chairman of Parliament
Alexander Moroz. 
</P>
